  "text": "Kolta et al. [CITATION_1] noted a significant correlation between vertebral anterior heights (h a ) and NTX/creatinine ratio, one of the key biochemical markers of bone resorption. They reported h a reduction with advancing age in postmenopausal women, but did not observe any significant change in premenopausal women.",
